President Obama expressed his appreciation for Senator Richard Lugar's service in the United States Senate. While they didn't always agree on everything, the President acknowledged Lugar's willingness to reach across the aisle and get things done. The President also credited Lugar's work in securing the world's most dangerous weapons and the bipartisan cooperation they forged during their first overseas trip together. Lugar's tradition of strong, bipartisan leadership on national security was commended, as it helped the United States prevail in the Cold War and sustain American leadership. The President wished Lugar all the best in his future endeavors.